The revelation was one that would shape Welsh’s career. Soon after those seminal sips, he began working behind the counter at the cafe. Today, he is Peet’s roastmaster.“Back then, it was rare to taste a beautifully sourced, perfectly roasted, expertly brewed, properly strong cup of coffee. That just wasn't a thing,” Welsh says. “Now, some 30 years later, it's amazing how much good coffee there is.”
